== Solar Sails

Solar sails do not use a mass driver, instead they generate thrust through the momentum change of photons. Each photon imparts an almost negligible amount of momentum ($approx 1.326 times 10^(-27) m k g "/" s$ per photon) and so solar sailing spacecraft must:

- Maximize the area of the sail to increase the number of incident photons.
- Must be incredibly light to maximize tha acceleration.

As there is no need for propellent and engines there can be a significant mass reduction, particularly for high $Delta V$ missions. Solar sails can also use an orientation strategy called tacking in order to vary its orbit, shown in *@21-tacking*.

