== Issues with Solar Sails

Solar sails cannot be used below 800km, due to their very high drag. They also cannot be used beyond 0.25 AU as the solar flux is too weak. They also present complex orbital mechanics issues and attitude control issues. Furthermore there exists a complex issue of folding up and deploying the whole structure.

== Solar Sail $I_(s p)$

A rough expression can be developed for the $I_(s p)$ of a solar sail, this expression is shown in *@21-solar-sail-isp*.

$
  I_(s p) = (a_0 T)/(g_0 ln(M_0/M_f))
$<21-solar-sail-isp>

Where $a_0$ is the spacecraft acceleration (thrust / total spacecraft mass) and $T$ is the mission duration. The final mass $M_f$ assumed the weight of the solar sail is removed. The $I_(s p)$ for various different accelerations is shown plotted against chemical and electrical propulsion methods in *@21-solar-sail-isp-plotted*.

