- *Square Sail*: Booms extend out from the spacecraft body and a rectangular sail unfurls.
- *Spinning Disk Sail*: The spacecraft spins and the solar sail expands out due to centrifugal force.
- *Heliogyro*: Rolls of sail extend out, these could then be angled to spin the spacecraft like a helicopter.

== Solar Sail Orbits and Further Uses of Solar Sails

Solar sails can fly in non-Keplerian orbits (spiral orbits, halo orbits). Solar sails are well suited to long interplanetary missions, reducing transit times to days.

Solar sails have been used for attitude control as well as to shine light onto the Earth. Interstellar microsailing exists as a possible method for interplanetary transport using lasers to accelerate a solar sail up to interplanetary speeds.

== Electric Sails

Instead of using the Sun's photons to impart momentum, electric sails use the Solar Wind which consists of charged particles moving very quickly. If a spacecraft has the opposite charge then it will be repelled by the solar wind and the sail would not need to be a full sail but tendrils instead.

